    "description": "The principal numbered extent is Padelford's 31 song sections. At XML-structure level those sections contain 31 direct source-song units with 186 LG and 717 L elements, while the interleaved apparatus contains 26 P elements, 68 further LG with 266 L, and four comparison L elements embedded in P, yielding 254 LG and 987 L overall. The prose-unit and verse-unit counts use different structural granularities and therefore are not summed to redefine the thirty-one numbered songs. These are encoded element counts, not canonical poem-line or stanza counts.",
